textBeforeTable: Names in Other Languages Witchyworld might be a parody of Disneyworld. The level itself may be a reference to Action Park[1] because it was an amusement park that was closed due to various injuries and deaths involving unsafe rides, a poor safety record, and negligent, as well as intoxicated staff. In the original manual that came with the game, it states: "...inside Grunty's rundown ammusment park...", meaning that the park is owned by Grunty. In the lobby of the Crazy Castle, by using the Beak Buster and getting the timing right, you can actually use the floor like a real bouncy house. The floor has a big bounce to it and will fling Banjo and Kazooie high into the air repeatedly. If you zap the control box (which is open) on the side of The Star Spinner's generator as Mumbo, Grunty will say "Stop it you vandal! You'll have to pay for any damage you know." -Grunty You don't actually have to pay for it though, it's just a joke. You cannot do this with other generators because their power boxes are closed. This world was originally intended for Banjo-Kazooie, but was pulled out due to time restrictions This is the only level in the game that doesn't have an underwater variation, although it is possible to go underwater in the pool under the Dive of Death.
